Add Omni Supervisor to the Classic Console

To add Omni Supervisor to the Salesforce classic console, follow these steps:

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Omni-Channel and manage apps.

Before adding Omni Supervisor:
 
Make sure you have Omni-Channel enabled with agents and queues running.
Make sure you have a working console app.

In Setup, enter Apps in the Quick Find box, then select Apps. Click Edit next to the classic console app that you want to add Omni Supervisor to, or create a new console app.

In the Choose Navigation Tab Items section, add Omni Supervisor to the Selected Items list.
Select the profiles you want to assign to this Supervisor-enabled console.
Click Save.

Verify that Omni Supervisor is in the console by opening it and viewing the tab selections.
title: Adding Omni Supervisor to Salesforce Classic Console
